<text\
xml:space="preserve">The\
'''2008\
Kosovo\
declaration\
of\
independence'''\
was\
an\
act\
of\
the\
[[Assembly\
of\
Kosovo]],\
adopted\
on\
17\
February\
2008,\
which\
declared\
that\
[[Kosovo]]\
was\
independent\
from\
[[Serbia]].&lt;ref&gt;placeholder&lt;/ref&gt;\
The\
declaration\
was\
the\
second\
declaration\
of\
independence\
by\
Kosovo's\
[[Albanian\
people|Albanian]]-dominated\
political\
institutions,\
the\
first\
having\
been\
on\
7\
September\
1990.&lt;ref&gt;Howard\
Clark,\
''Civil\
Resistance\
in\
Kosovo'',\
p.\
73.\
Pluto\
Press,\
2000.\
ISBN\
0745315690&lt;/ref&gt;\
Unlike\
the\
[[1990\
Kosovo\
declaration\
of\
independence]],\
which\
only\
[[Albania]]\
recognised,&lt;ref&gt;''ibid'',\
p.\
92&lt;/ref&gt;\
Kosovo's\
second\
declaration\
of\
independence\
was\
expected\
to\
be\
widely\
supported\
by\
foreign\
states\
including\
most\
[[European\
Union]]\
member\
states,\
the\
[[United\
Nations]]\
and\
most\
of\
the\
other\
states\
of\
the\
[[Socialist\
Federal\
Republic\
of\
Yugoslavia|former\
Yugoslavia]].&lt;ref&gt;placeholder&lt;/ref&gt;

Kosovo's\
declaration\
of\
independence\
was\
extremely\
controversial,\
as\
it\
was\
opposed\
by\
Serbia\
and\
its\
main\
ally\
[[Russia]].\
The\
newly\
proclaimed\
Republic\
of\
Kosova\
has\
not\
been\
seated\
at\
the\
[[United\
Nations]],\
as\
it\
is\
generally\
believed\
that\
any\
application\
for\
UN\
membership\
would\
be\
blocked\
by\
Russia\
out\
of\
sympathy\
for\
Serbia.&lt;ref\
name=&quot;sdut150208&quot;&gt;&quot;[http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/world/20080215-0733-kosovo-serbia-russia-response.html\
Russia's\
options\
limited\
for\
Kosovo\
retaliation&quot;],\
''San\
Diego\
Union-Tribune'',\
February\
15,\
2008&lt;/ref&gt;\
Serbia\
and\
Russia\
both\
regard\
Kosovo's\
declaration\
of\
independence\
as\
illegal\
and\
its\
recognition\
as\
a\
violation\
of\
[[international\
law]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/6324673.stm\
Serbia\
rejects\
Kosovo\
breakaway]&quot;,\
BBC\
News\
Online,\
February\
2,\
2007&lt;/ref&gt;\
Russia\
has\
vowed\
to\
oppose\
Kosovo's\
independence\
with\
a\
&quot;plan\
of\
retaliation&quot;\
that\
some\
have\
suggested\
could\
see\
Russia\
recognising\
the\
hitherto\
internationally\
unrecognised\
breakaway\
states\
of\
[[Abkhazia]]\
and\
[[South\
Ossetia]]\
in\
[[Georgia]].&lt;ref\
name=&quot;sdut150208&quot;\
/&gt;\
Serbia\
has\
likewise\
vowed\
to\
oppose\
Kosovo's\
independence\
with\
a\
package\
of\
measures\
intended\
to\
discourage\
the\
international\
recognition\
of\
the\
republic.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5juNm3C14Y4oWmhBjjfv41_OuYnXAD8UQRMOO1\
Serbian\
President\
Vows\
Fight\
Over\
Kosovo]&quot;,\
Associated\
Press,\
February\
15,\
2008&lt;/ref&gt;

